#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "45. Rahonisajjasikkhāpada"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 45: the training rule on sitting down in private"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.45.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.360"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa919"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto sahāyakassa gharaṃ gantvā tassa pajāpatiyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappesi."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Upananda the Sakyan went to the house of a friend and sat down in private alone with his wife."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Atha kho so puriso ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "The husband complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma ayyo upanando mayhaṃ pajāpatiyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda sit down in private alone with my wife?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa920"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa purisassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of that man,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto mātugāmena saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappessatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda sit down in private alone with a woman?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, mātugāmena saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmena saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappessasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you sit down in private alone with a woman?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pāsādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa921"></a>
#. <strong class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmena saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk sits down in private alone with a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </strong>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "(<em>45</em>:<strong>94</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.45.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa922"></a>
#. <strong class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <strong class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa923"></a>
#. <strong class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Mātugāmo nāma"
msgstr "A woman:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "manussitthī, na yakkhī na petī na tiracchānagatā, viññū paṭibalā subhāsitadubbhāsitaṃ duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ ājānituṃ."
msgstr "a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal. She understands and is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, what is lewd and what is not lewd."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.361"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa924"></a>
#. <strong class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "Saddhinti"
msgstr "With:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "ekato."
msgstr "together."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa925"></a>
#. <strong class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "Eko ekāyāti"
msgstr "Alone:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "bhikkhu ceva hoti mātugāmo ca."
msgstr "just the monk and the woman."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa926"></a>
#. <strong class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Raho nāma"
msgstr "In private:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "cakkhussa raho, sotassa raho."
msgstr "there is private to the eye and there is private to the ear."

#. <strong class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "Cakkhussa raho nāma"
msgstr "Private to the eye:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "na sakkā hoti akkhiṃ vā nikhaṇīyamāne bhamukaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne sīsaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne passituṃ."
msgstr "one is unable to see them winking, raising an eyebrow, or nodding."

#. </span>
#. <strong class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "Sotassa raho nāma"
msgstr "Private to the ear:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "na sakkā hoti pakatikathā sotuṃ."
msgstr "one is unable to hear ordinary speech."

#. </span></span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa927"></a>
#. <strong class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "Nisajjaṃ kappeyyāti"
msgstr "Sits down:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid "mātugāme nisinne bhikkhu upanisinno vā hoti upanipanno vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if the monk sits down or lies down next to a seated woman, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "Bhikkhu nisinne mātugāmo upanisinno vā hoti upanipanno vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If a woman sits down or lies down next to the seated monk, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "Ubho vā nisinnā honti ubho vā nipannā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If both are seated or both are lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.45.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa928"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Mātugāme mātugāmasaññī eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a woman, and he perceives her as a woman, and he sits down in private alone with her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "Mātugāme vematiko eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a woman, but he is unsure if it is, and he sits down in private alone with her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Mātugāme amātugāmasaññī eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as a woman, and he sits down in private alone with her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa929"></a>
#. VAR: tiracchānagatamanussaviggahitthiyā → tiracchā­na­gatāya vā ­manus­sa­vigga­hitthiyā vā (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Yakkhiyā vā petiyā vā paṇḍakena vā tiracchānagatamanussaviggahitthiyā vā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he sits down in private alone with a female spirit, with a female ghost, with a sexual nonconformist, or with a female animal in the form of a woman, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Amātugāme mātugāmasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not a woman, but he perceives it as a woman, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Amātugāme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Amātugāme amātugāmasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive it as a woman, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.45.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa930"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "yo koci viññū puriso dutiyo hoti,    "
msgstr "if he has a man who understands as a companion;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "tiṭṭhati na nisīdati,"
msgstr "if he stands and does not sit down;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "arahopekkho"
msgstr "if he is not seeking privacy;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "aññavihito nisīdati,"
msgstr "if he sits down thinking of something else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa931"></a>
#. VAR: Rahonisajjasikkhāpadaṃ → dutiya­raho­nisaj­ja­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc45:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "Rahonisajjasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr "The fifth rule, the training rule on sitting in private, is finished."

